. Counters and other effects aren\'t copied. Notably, if you copy a land that is also a creature because of a temporary effect (such as Celestial Colonnade), Thespian\'s Stage will become just the “unanimated” land.',33737),('No enters-the-battlefield abilities of the land Thespian\'s Stage is copying will trigger. Thespian\'s Stage was already on the battlefield.',33738),('The +3/+3 is also only until end of turn.',33739),('You can keep green mana in your mana pool indefinitely while Omnath is on the battlefield. That means if you add a green mana to your mana pool during one step or phase, you can spend it during a later step or phase, or even a later turn. Other types of mana will continue to empty from your mana pool as each step and phase ends.',33740),('If a green mana you add to your mana pool has certain restrictions or riders associated with it (for example, if it was produced by Ancient Ziggurat), they\'ll apply to that mana no matter when you spend it.',33741),('Once Omnath leaves the battlefield, you have until the end of the current step or phase to spend whatever green mana is in your mana pool before it too empties as normal. There is no penalty associated with this other than the loss of the mana.',33742),('The bonus is not applied until after you check for attack legality, so it is a 2/3 creature when declaring attackers.',33743),('The ability counts the number of attacking creatures with the creature type Aurochs, not just those named Aurochs.',33744),('Regeneration abilities that would affect that creature can still be activated; they just won’t do anything. The creature can’t be regenerated for any reason, even if an effect other than Incinerate would deal lethal damage to it or otherwise destroy it.',33745),('Can\'t acquire the Ante cards. They are considered still \"in the game\" as are cards in the library and the graveyard.',33746),('The choice is optional.',33747),('If you fail to find something, you still exile this.',33748),('Can\'t acquire cards that are phased out.',33749),('You can\'t acquire exiled cards because those cards are still in one of the game\'s zones.',33750),('In a sanctioned event, a card that\'s \"outside the game\" is one that\'s in your sideboard. In an unsanctioned event, you may choose any card from your collection.',33751),('Repeating the process includes the instruction to repeat the process. That is, the opponent will keep sacrificing permanents until he or she sacrifices a land.',33752),('Repeating the process does not include targeting an opponent. Only one opponent will have to sacrifice permanents.',33753),('If any abilities trigger while Tyrant of Discord’s enters-the-battlefield ability is resolving, those abilities will wait until the enters-the-battlefield ability finishes resolving before going on the stack. Starting with the active player, each player puts his or her abilities on the stack in any order.',33754),('If the target opponent can’t sacrifice permanents (perhaps because of Sigarda, Host of Herons), the opponent will choose a permanent at random but not sacrifice it. The ability will then finish resolving.',33755),('You choose the color during resolution. This means your opponent does not get to react after knowing the color you chose.',33756),('You must choose two targets. You can’t cast Victimize targeting only one creature card.',33757),('The creature you sacrifice isn’t chosen until Victimize resolves. You can’t return the creature you sacrifice because it will still be on the battlefield at the time targets are chosen.',33758),('As Victimize resolves, you must sacrifice a creature if able. You can’t change your mind and choose not to sacrifice anything.',33759),('If one of the targeted creature cards is an illegal target (for instance, because it has left your graveyard before Victimize resolves), you’ll still sacrifice a creature and put the other card onto the battlefield. If both are illegal targets, Victimize will be countered. You won’t sacrifice a