ower that start to apply after Riptide Mangler’s ability resolves will overwrite this effect.',38322),('Effects that modify Riptide Mangler’s power, such as the effect of Giant Growth or Glorious Anthem, will apply to Riptide Mangler no matter when they started applying. The same is true for counters that affect Riptide Mangler’s power and effects that switch its power and toughness.',38323),('The +1/+1 counter isn\'t put on the creature in time to increase the amount of combat damage dealt during that combat step.',38324),('If this creature deals combat damage to multiple players simultaneously, perhaps because some combat damage was redirected, its ability will trigger for each of those players.',38325),('Engulfing Slagwurm\'s ability triggers and resolves during the declare blockers step. Creatures destroyed this way will not deal combat damage.',38326),('If your Engulfing Slagwurm blocks or becomes blocked by multiple creatures, its ability triggers that many times. Each trigger will be associated with a specific creature. You choose which order to have the abilities resolve.',38327),('If Engulfing Slagwurm\'s ability resolves and the other creature is not destroyed (perhaps because it has already left the battlefield or it regenerates), you\'ll still gain life equal to that creature\'s toughness.',38328),('As each ability resolves, the amount of life you gain is equal to the appropriate creature\'s current toughness (if it\'s somehow still on the battlefield), or its toughness as it last existed on the battlefield (in all other cases).',38329),('Even if the ability of an attacking Engulfing Slagwurm destroys each creature blocking it, Engulfing Slagwurm won\'t deal combat damage to the player or planeswalker it\'s attacking unless it somehow gains trample.',38330),('If blockers have already been declared when Stoneshock Giant’s last ability resolves, those blocks won’t change or become undone.',38331),('Your opponents can’t assign any creature without flying to