oose a pile each time. Only creatures that were in both of the chosen piles can attack.',39784),('The effect is best understood if you read it as \"creatures not in the chosen pile can\'t attack.\"',39785),('Intimidate looks at the current colors of a creature that has it. Normally, Bladetusk Boar can\'t be blocked except by artifact creatures and/or red creatures. If it\'s turned blue, then it can\'t be blocked except by artifact creatures and/or blue creatures.',39786),('The -1/-1 counters you remove don’t have to be the same counters put on the creature by Shambling Swarm.',39787),('The value of X is determined when Rush of Blood resolves. The bonus won’t change later in the turn if the creature’s power changes.',39788),('If the creature has power less than 0, the “bonus” will be negative. For example, a creature that’s somehow become -1/3 would get -1/+0 and become -2/3.',39789),('This card has received errata so that it now targets a specific opponent.',39790),('The count of the number of black permanents the targeted opponent controls is done during announcement since it only affects target selection. It does not get recounted later.',39791),('The value of X is determined as the activated ability resolves. If the equipped creature isn’t on the battlefield at that time, use its power the last time it was on the battlefield to determine the value of X. If that power was negative, other creatures you control will lose power and toughness. For example, if the equipped creature was 2/2 and a spell gave it -5/-5 in response to Dragon Throne of Tarkir’s activated ability, other creatures you control would get -3/-3 until end of turn.',39792),('This effect reverses the turn order established at the beginning of the game. While the order is reversed, anything that cares about this order (such as determining in what order choices are made) will use the new reversed',39793),('If the game\'s turn order is reversed again, it will return to the default order used at the beg