n, then sacrifice this card.',40847),('This ability is targeted, so Protection can prevent targeting if it exists when the ability would be put on the stack. Once the ability is on the stack, adding Protection will not counter the ability but the exchange will not take place since the target is illegal and you sacrifice this card on resolution.',40848),('You choose Reality Spasm’s mode as you cast it.',40849),('You may target any permanents with Reality Spasm, regardless of whether they’re tapped or untapped.',40850),('You choose the color on resolution. Your opponent does not get to respond between the color choice and the damage happening. They need to use any damage prevention they want before you choose a color.',40851),('Destroying or unequipping the Echo Circlet after blockers have been declared will not undo any blocks made by the equipped creature.',40852),('Echo Circlet\'s effect is cumulative. If it equips a creature that can already block an additional creature, now it can block three creatures. The same is true if two Echo Circlets equip the same creature, for example.',40853),('The affected land loses its existing land types and any abilities printed on it. It becomes the chosen basic land type and now has the ability to tap to add one mana of the appropriate color to your mana pool. Unstable Frontier\'s ability doesn\'t change the affected land\'s name or whether it\'s legendary or basic.',40854),('You must target a creature and a land in order to cast Grip of Desolation. A permanent that’s both a land and a creature can be chosen for both targets.',40855),('The -1/-1 is not permanent. It lasts until the end of the turn as do the abilities that are granted.',40856),('This spell can target any creature. The check for whether that creature is attacking or blocking made on resolution, and it will have the appropriate effect at that time.',40857),('If the creature is neither an attacking creature nor a blocking creature at the time the spell resolves, it will have no effect.',40858),('This ability triggers off anyone casting a spell, including you, not just Desecration Elemental’s controller or an opponent.',40859),('If Desecration Elemental is the only creature you control when its triggered ability resolves, you’ll have to sacrifice it.',40860),('The ability will trigger if you don\'t control an enchantment, even for a brief moment during the resolution of another spell or ability.',40861),('Only checks if you control no enchantments at the time it triggers. It does not check again on resolution. Gaining control of an enchantment before then will not save the Griffin.',40862),('A card is “directly above” another card in your graveyard if it was put into that graveyard later and there are no cards in between the two.',40863),('Abilities that reduce the cost of a spell apply after abilities that raise them. For example, Borrowed Malevolence with both modes chosen costs {1}{B} to cast if you control Voracious Reader.',40864),('If an instant or sorcery spell has {X} in its mana cost, choose the value for X first, and then reduce the cost by {1}. For example, Dark Salvation with X chosen as 2 costs {3}{B} to cast if you control Voracious Reader.',40865),('Brittle Effigy is exiled as a cost to activate its ability, not as part of its effect. If the targeted creature is an illegal target by the time the ability would resolve, the ability is countered, but Brittle Effigy remains exiled.',40866),('The first ability applies only if your life total is being reduced by damage. Other effects or costs (such as “lose 1 life” or “pay 1 life\") can reduce your life total below 1 as normal.',40867),('The last sentence is not a prevention effect. It stops unpreventable damage from reducing your life total below 1.',40868),('Thief won’t prevent you from losing the game if your life total is 0 or less or some other effect causes you to lose the game.',40869),('You can target any artifact, not just one with an ability that references ch