he next ability will untap it as well (and so on).',41233),('For Amulet of Vigor\'s ability to trigger, a permanent must enter the battlefield tapped due to an effect that says \"put [the permanent] onto the battlefield tapped,\" \"[this permanent] enters the battlefield tapped,\" or the like. If it enters the battlefield untapped, the ability won\'t trigger, even if you tap that permanent afterward.',41234),('You may pay {B} only once. The target player will discard a maximum of one card because of Drainpipe Vermin’s ability.',41235),('All Suns’ Dawn can have from zero to five targets, one for each color.',41236),('You can target two blue-and-white multicolored cards by choosing one as the blue card and one as the white card.',41237),('You choose the color each target must be when you choose it as a target, so if the card you targeted as a blue card is red when All Suns’ Dawn resolves, the card is an illegal target, even if the spell doesn’t target another red card.',41238),('If Higure deals regular combat damage and you use its ability to search for another Ninja, that card won\'t be in your hand in time to activate its ninjutsu ability to put it onto the battlefield and deal damage. However, the card you searched for could still be swapped for an unblocked creature, including Higure, as long as you activate its ninjutsu ability before the end of combat.',41239),('If Higure deals first strike damage (or the first part of double strike damage), the triggered ability would resolve before regular combat damage, and the searched-for Ninja would be able to get swapped with an unblocked creature and still deal its regular damage.',41240),('You can’t discard more than once to target more than one creature (or player) or to do multiple amounts of damage to a single creature (or player).',41241),('Mycoid Shepherd’s ability will trigger when it’s put into a graveyard from the battlefield no matter what its power is at that time.',41242),('If another creature you control is 