n from any other quality Sheltering Ancient has.',44105),('Your starting life total is the life total you began the game with. For most two-player formats, this is 20. For Two-Headed Giant, it\'s the life total your team started with, usually 30. In Commander games, the starting life total is 40.',44106),('You check your life total to see if Chalice of Life transforms only when its ability resolves.',44107),('Guardian’s effect doesn’t wear off.',44108),('After the triggered ability resolves, Opal Guardian is no longer an enchantment.',44109),('A face-down creature spell will cause Opal Guardian’s ability to trigger (if it’s an enchantment).',44110),('Each player must exile the top card of his or her library at the start of each upkeep step.',44111),('Each time there’s a tie for the highest cost, only the players involved in the tie continue.',44112),('If a player fails to exile a card, he or she can’t take the extra turn.',44113),('If multiple extra turns are created in a game, the most recently created extra turn is taken first.',44114),('Remember which player would have taken the next turn if Timesifter’s ability hadn’t triggered the first time. After Timesifter leaves the battlefield and all extra turns have been taken, that player takes the next turn.',44115),('If two or more Timesifters are on the battlefield, keep a careful record of which players get which extra turns. With two Timesifters on the battlefield, two extra turns are created for each turn taken.',44116),('A land card has a converted mana cost of 0.',44117),('You can’t force an opponent to discard a card he or she casts by activating the last ability in response. The spell is on the stack by then.',44118),('The enchanted land untaps at the same time as the active player’s permanents. You can’t choose to not untap it at that time.',44119),('Effects that state that the enchanted land doesn’t untap during your untap step won’t apply during another player’s untap step.',44120),('If a player controls tw